definition.value: A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of estrone 3-O-(3-sulfo-beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic and sulfate groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of 5beta-pregnane 3alpha,20alpha-diol 3-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic group; major species at pH 7.3.

A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of 5beta-pregnane 3alpha,20alpha-diol 3-O-(3-sulfo-beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic and sulfate groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of testosterone 17-O-(3-sulfo-beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic and sulfate groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of dehydroepiandrosterone 3-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic group; major species at pH 7.3.

A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of dehydroepiandrosterone 3-O-(3-sulfo-beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic and sulfate groups; major species at pH 7.3.

A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of 5beta-androstane-3alpha,17alpha-diol-11-one-17beta-carboxylate 3-O-(beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic groups; major species at pH 7.3.

A steroid glucuronide anion that is the conjugate base of 5beta-androstane-3alpha,17alpha-diol-11-one-17beta-carboxylate 3-O-(3-sulfo-beta-D-glucuronide) arising from deprotonation of the carboxylic and sulfate groups; major species at pH 7.3.
A member of the class of pteridines that is pteridine substituted by an amino group at position 2 and hydroxy groups at positions 4, 6 and 7.
An aminoalcohol that is N(1)-(5-aminopentyl)pentane-1,5-diamine substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 2, 2', 4 and 4' (the 2R,4S,2'R,4'S-stereoisomer).
An 8-heptadecenal in which the double bond at position 8 adopts a trans-configuration.
An aryl beta-D-glucoside that is salicyl alcohol in which the phenolic hydrogen has been replaced by a beta-D-glucosyl residue.
